  "text": "The SpiderMonkey JS-to-bytecode pipeline flows through these key files: (1) **BytecodeCompiler.cpp/.h** is the top-level entry point \u2014 functions like `CompileGlobalScript` and `CompileGlobalScriptToStencilAndMaybeInstantiate` orchestrate the full compile pipeline. (2) **TokenStream.cpp/.h** provides lexical analysis, tokenizing JS source text. (3) **Parser.cpp/.h** implements the recursive-descent parser via the `GeneralParser` template class hierarchy (ParserSharedBase \u2192 ParserBase \u2192 PerHandlerParser \u2192 GeneralParser \u2192 Parser). (4) **ParseNode.h/.cpp** defines AST node types \u2014 the `FOR_EACH_PARSE_NODE_KIND` macro enumerates all node kinds (expressions, statements, etc.) and maps them to C++ node classes (UnaryNode, BinaryNode, ListNode, etc.). **FullParseHandler.h** creates these ParseNode instances during full parsing. (5) **BytecodeEmitter.cpp/.h** walks the parse tree and emits bytecode, with **BytecodeSection.cpp/.h** managing the bytecode buffer and per-script data. (6) **Stencil.cpp/.h** defines the `CompilationStencil` intermediate representation that captures compilation output in a GC-free form. (7) **vm/JSScript.cpp/.h** defines `BaseScript`/`JSScript` \u2014 the runtime representation holding the final bytecode (accessed via `SharedImmutableScriptData`). **vm/Opcodes.h** defines all bytecode opcodes via the `FOR_EACH_OPCODE` macro.",
